вЂЋВ В В  <p>At the very heart of Monster, the series delves deep into our psyche, into the realm that brings out a certain type of horror. The question it raises is whether a monster lurks in every one of us, how it can be manipulated, and how we may finally overcome it to become a better person. Some people find it quickly, while others, like Eva, suffer much before they truly change for the better. But it never mattered who in particular the story focuses upon, for each and every story arc was profound, filled with tragedy, but ultimately redemption. That a character can be brought to the lowest depths imaginable but then saved or redeemed... those scenes were what delivered such a strong emotional impact for me. Even now, certain scenes still come back to me, clear as the day I watched it.</p>В В В  
